The paper focuses on developing a convolutional neural network for action recognition in videos, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning methods (cs.LG) and feature enhancing techniques (cs.MM) to improve the performance of the model. Additionally, the proposed re-ranking technique involves exploiting the relationship among action classes, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
